    "docContent": {
      "p2": "<h2>Purpose</h2><p>This example shows how a Documentation Page can hold longer explanatory material that does not belong inside a single box.</p><h2>Assumptions</h2><ul><li>Community priorities have been gathered through a suitable engagement process.</li><li>Grant criteria should be clear enough for both applicants and assessors.</li><li>The documentation page should support the board structure, not replace the This–Then logic.</li></ul><h2>Review notes</h2><p>Before using this as a real board, replace example text with project-specific evidence, assumptions, risks, and decision rules.</p>"
